Two men, Ibrahim Issa, 27 and Haruna Mohammed, 30, were on Friday arraigned in an Ogudu Magistrates’ Court, Lagos, for alleged attempted murder. Issa and Haruna, whose addresses were not given, are facing a four-count charge of conspiracy, attempted murder, assault occasioning harm and threat to life. READ ALSO:  House wife in court for allegedly stealing pair of women’s slippers They however, pleaded not guilty to the charges of conspiracy, assault and threat to life, while on the charge of attempted murder, a plea was not taken. The Prosecutor, Insp. Donjor Perezi, told the court that the defendants and others still at large, committed the offences on Dec. 27, 2019, at about 11.40 a.m., at Mile 12 Market, Lagos. Perezi said that the defendants, during a heated argument with the complainant, Abubakar Mohammed, used a broken bottle and cutlass to inflict near fatal injuries on his head. “They also used a big rod to injure him on his head and neck. “They assaulted another complainant-Aliyu Abubakar, who came to help Mohammed by beating him with the same big stick all over his body. “The defendants threatened to kill Mohammed and Abubakar if they ever messed with them again,” he alleged. According to the prosecutor, the offences contravened sections 56, 173, 230 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos, 2015. The Magistrate, Mrs Bukola Mogaji, granted each of the defendants bail in the sum of N500, 000, with two sureties each in like sum on the charges of conspiracy, assault and threat to life. Mogaji, however, denied the defendants bail on the charge of attempted murder. She ordered that the sureties must reside within the court’s jurisdiction and be gainfully employed, with evidence of tax payment to the Lagos State Government. The case was adjourned until Jan. 31, 2019 for further hearing.